 never been asked by any inquiry or investigation about this.

'Now you’re asking me about them, I’m quite happy to answer and get everything out in the open.’

The jury has previously heard that the
 Metropolitan Police launched an investigation into phone hacking at the
 News of the World after the Royal Household raised the alarm.

Prosecutor Andrew Edis QC, told the 
jurors the 2006 investigation was more limited than the later police 
inquiry, Operation Weeting, launched in 2011.

Goodman, of Addlestone, Surrey, said 
he first targeted Miss Middleton amid speculation her relationship with 
Prince William was becoming more serious, and that Mulcaire had provided
 her phone details.

He told the Old Bailey: ‘I’m really 
not the slightest bit proud of this.

