The journalist said Mulcaire’s role at
 the News of the World was well known at the paper, adding: ‘Virtually 
every story that went through the paper was ground through Glenn 
Mulcaire’s phone hacking mill.’

Coulson, 45, and Goodman both deny conspiracy to commit misconduct by paying public officials for Palace phone directories.

Coulson and former News International chief executive Rebekah Brooks both deny conspiracy to hack phones.

